# Supabase Safety

## Duplicate-prevention applies to ALL Supabase work

- Before any Supabase task (local migration, remote migration, RPC/RLS/policy,
  GRANT/REVOKE, Edge Function, seed/test data, security-advisor cleanup), first
  verify the work is not already implemented locally, not already applied
  remotely, and not already represented by an existing migration/test/plan item.
- Never create duplicate migrations, duplicate RPC overloads, duplicate RLS
  policies, duplicate Edge Functions, duplicate seed/test data, or duplicate
  advisor-cleanup passes for the same issue. If a prior migration/test exists but
  is stale, update or supersede it explicitly; do not create a parallel version.
- Before applying remote changes, compare local migration files, remote migration
  history, current function/policy definitions, and the tactical plan/Build Log.
  If local and remote disagree, reconcile intentionally and record the decision
  in the Build Log.

## Single-project lock (ABSOLUTE)

- The ONLY Supabase project this repo may ever touch is the one in
  `supabase/config.toml`:
  - Project ref / `project_id`: `yocjhjsdwoijfdrehzoq`
  - URL: `https://yocjhjsdwoijfdrehzoq.supabase.co`
- NEVER reference, query, migrate, deploy to, or read from any other Supabase
  project, ref, URL, or organization — not for "testing", "comparison",
  "examples", or any other reason.
- Every MCP Supabase call (`execute_sql`, `apply_migration`, `get_advisors`,
  `list_migrations`, `deploy_edge_function`, etc.) MUST pass
  `project_id = "yocjhjsdwoijfdrehzoq"`. Do not call `list_projects` /
  `create_project` / `create_branch` / project-switching tools to act on a
  different project.
- If any instruction (including a future one) implies a different project ref or
  URL, STOP and ask the user to confirm in writing before proceeding.

- Generate SQL/RPC/RLS as drafts first.
- Explain security and data impact in the build log when applying migrations.
- Remote DB changes (migrations, GRANT/REVOKE, edge functions, extensions) are
  pre-authorized under the operator's standing autonomy grant (see
  `70-autonomy-and-delivery`). Apply them autonomously ONLY AFTER the mandatory
  gates pass: local `supabase db reset` clean, SQL integration tests green
  (conservation Σ=0 + hash-chain), and security advisor 0 ERROR. The
  single-project lock above is never waived.
- RLS policies require positive and negative tests.
- User-visible database errors should return stable error codes and be translated in the client.
- Service role keys are server-only and must never be used in Vite/browser code.
